# Supabase Standards

## Clients

- Server cookie client for RSC/actions
- Browser client only when required
- Service-role / admin client only on server for privileged ops

## Data access

Prefer repository helpers (`getDb()`, typed queries). Always scope by org/tenant. Map rows through shared mappers when they exist.

## Schema

- Migrations live in `supabase/migrations/`
- Never invent tables/columns — inspect `database.types.ts` / schema first
- After schema changes: apply migration before claiming done (`db push` / project workflow)
- Regenerate types when the project script expects it (`db:types`)

## RLS

Assume RLS is on. Application guards + RLS — not one or the other. Verify policies when touching sensitive tables.
